The authorities of the Obafemi Awolowo University, Ile Ife, have announced that the second group of students, of the under-listed departments, are expected on campus for the practical contents of their respective courses, from Monday, 29th of March to Friday, 16th of April, 2021. A statement by the Public Relations Officer of the University, Abiodun Olarewaju, listed the Departments as follows: 1. Agriculture – Parts 1 to 3, 5 2. Arts – *Department of Music, Parts 1-4 * Department of Foreign Languages, Parts 1,2, & 4. * Students offering these courses: EGL 103, EGL 201, EGL 301, DRA 103, DRA 209, DRA 105, DRA 307, DRA 413, DRA 423,DRA 427 3. EDM – Parts 1 to 5 4. Technology -Parts 1 to 5 5. Education: Students offering these courses: BOT101, BOT103, CHM101, CHM103, ZOO103, BOT201. CHM205, CHM207, CSC301, ZOO201,BOT203, BOT301, BOT303, ZOO301, BOT305, ZOI401, ZOO403,CHM101, CHM103, PHY101, PHY107, CHM201, CHM203, CHM205, PHY203, CHM305, CHM307, CHM309, CSC201, CHM401, PHY201, PHY203, PHY205, PHY207, PHY301, PHY303, PHY305, PHY307 PHY401, PHY405, PHY431, MTH101, MTH201, MTH205, MTH207, MTH311, MTH305, MTH423, MTH401, MTH403, MTG409, MTH417, CSC 331, CSC221, PHE101, PHE201, PHE301, PHE405, PHE411, PHE111, PHE213, PHE209 6. Social Sciences: Students offering these courses: CSC 333, PSY 205, GPY 205, GPY 303, GPY 417 , GPY 419 All students should strictly observe COVID-19 protocols in and outside the campus. YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE We Have Not Had Water Supply In Months ― Abeokuta Residents In spite of the huge investment in the water sector by the government and international organisations, water scarcity has grown to become a perennial nightmare for residents of Abeokuta, the Ogun State capital. This report x-rays the lives and experiences of residents in getting clean, potable and affordable water amidst the surge of COVID-19 cases in the state. OAU Resumption: Second group expected on Monday Selfies, video calls and Chinese documenta